A '''double inverted pendulum''' is the combination of the [[inverted pendulum]] and the [[double pendulum]]. The double inverted pendulum is unstable, meaning that it will fall down unless it is controlled in some way. The two main methods of controlling a double inverted pendulum are moving the base, as with the inverted pendulum, or by applying a torque at the pivot point between the two pendulums.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.cs.berkeley.edu/~pabbeel/cs287-fa09/readings/Tedrake-Aug09.pdf | title = Underactuated Robotics: Learning, Planning, and Control for Efficient and Agile Machines, Course Notes for MIT 6.832 | author = Russ Tedrake | publisher = [[University of California, Berkeley]] | date = 2009 | accessdate = 2011-10-05}}</ref>
