{{Fusion devices |name = Uragan-2M |image = |type = [[Stellarator]] |major radius = 170 cm |minor radius = 24 cm |field = 2.4 [[Tesla (unit)|T]] |operation = <!-- YYYY– --> |location = [[Kharkov]], [[Ukraine]] }} '''Uragan-2M''' (U-2M, {{lang-uk|Ураган-2М}}) is a [[stellarator]] (magnetic plasma confinement, [[controlled thermonuclear fusion]] experiment) installed at the Institute of Plasma Physics National Science Center, which is part of the [[Kharkiv Institute of Physics and Technology]] (IFS KIPT) in [[Kharkov]], [[Ukraine]]. It is the largest [[stellarator]] (torsatron) in Europe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.logos.biz.ua/proj/vynahid/online/97.htm|publisher=National Institute of Plasma Physics Research Center [Інститут фізики плазми Національного наукового центру]|title= Харківський фізико-технічний інститут|trans-title=Kharkiv Institute of Physics and Technology|series = NAS Ukraine [НАН України]}}</ref>
== Specifications== Uragan-2M is a medium-sized [[stellarator]] with reduced helical corrugations. The unit has a torus radius of {{convert|170|cm|abbr=in}}, a plasma radius of up to {{convert|24|cm|abbr=in}}, and a toroidal [[magnetic field]] of up to {{convert|2.4|T}}.
